helm create sample chart

Ls
   
Chart.yaml	charts		templates	values.yaml


helm-2.13.1 install --name helm.test1 ./samplechart --set service.type=LoadBalancer


helm list


kubectl get services
    
        helm-test1.samplechart


Then you get a external ip then copy it and add it to curl


curl 192.168.0.1

         then you get nginx welcome page which means the service is up-end running


You can also check through following commands

kubectl get pods

kubectl get deployments


